WEBVTT

00:03.235 --> 00:05.131
You say you want a
box of chocolates

00:05.155 --> 00:06.883
or a lousy bunch of flowers?

00:06.907 --> 00:09.260
Better say pretty please with
your life savings on top.

00:09.284 --> 00:10.678
Because on this day,

00:10.702 --> 00:12.638
they have a gun to your
girlfriend's heart.

00:12.662 --> 00:14.640
We get it, Bailey. You're
not into the holiday.

00:14.664 --> 00:16.225
Do you want me to set a
place for your grandfather?

00:16.248 --> 00:17.518
No. He's away on business.

00:17.542 --> 00:18.978
So, what are you guys doing?

00:19.002 --> 00:20.980
Well, Justin's
planning something,

00:21.004 --> 00:22.356
but he won't tell me what it is.

00:22.380 --> 00:24.859
A surprise? That is so romantic.

00:24.883 --> 00:27.361
Because you want to make
reservations at a restaurant,

00:27.385 --> 00:29.363
you better be, like,
related to the president.

00:29.387 --> 00:31.574
So does that mean that
you're not making any plans

00:31.598 --> 00:33.691
or reservations for us
for Valentine's Day?

00:35.143 --> 00:37.070
Why are you smiling?

00:37.604 --> 00:39.874
Should I ask, or
is it a surprise?

00:39.898 --> 00:42.627
Sarah. You are gonna love this.

00:42.651 --> 00:44.545
Once you see how much fun it is.

00:44.569 --> 00:47.340
Once you take your
seat Wednesday night,

00:47.364 --> 00:48.799
23rd row center.

00:48.823 --> 00:51.093
You, me, Will, Gina.

00:51.117 --> 00:53.503
Will and Gina? Okay.

00:53.620 --> 00:56.140
Live at the county stadium,
it's the third annual,

00:56.164 --> 00:59.092
grand championship
monster truck show!

01:01.211 --> 01:03.439
Monster truck show?

01:03.463 --> 01:06.150
Sarah, the mighty,
fighting flatbeds,

01:06.174 --> 01:09.352
spraying mud all the way
back to the 50th row.

01:09.844 --> 01:11.030
On Valentine's Day.

01:11.054 --> 01:12.605
Yes!

01:13.014 --> 01:15.201
Well, maybe a really
nice dinner beforehand.

01:15.225 --> 01:17.453
Yeah, yeah. That would work.
That would be great.

01:17.477 --> 01:20.071
What... What is...

01:20.397 --> 01:22.031
Are you not excited?

01:22.273 --> 01:24.627
Well, Bay, it's not the,
you know, the truck show,

01:24.651 --> 01:26.796
because that sounds,
you know, great.

01:26.820 --> 01:29.173
It's just... This is my
first Valentine's Day

01:29.197 --> 01:30.591
with an actual boyfriend,

01:30.615 --> 01:32.385
and I'd kind of like
to spend it with him

01:32.409 --> 01:34.428
you know, doing
something romantic.

01:34.452 --> 01:37.765
So, what is your point?

01:37.789 --> 01:40.142
My point is, this,
this truck thing.

01:40.166 --> 01:41.843
This is your idea of romantic?

01:42.168 --> 01:45.648
Sarah, look. My idea
of romantic is...

01:45.672 --> 01:48.057
Is, is naming a star after you.

01:48.883 --> 01:49.986
My idea of romantic is...

01:50.010 --> 01:52.154
Is taking a punch in the gut

01:52.178 --> 01:53.948
to win you back from
my best friend.

01:53.972 --> 01:57.034
My idea of romantic is my idea.

01:57.058 --> 02:00.361
When I have it. Not when
the calendar tells me to.

02:01.604 --> 02:02.540
Julia.

02:02.564 --> 02:04.532
Does this mean
you're not coming?

02:06.276 --> 02:07.294
Jule.

02:07.318 --> 02:08.336
It would be fun.

02:08.360 --> 02:09.630
Can you come out here for a sec?

02:09.654 --> 02:11.924
Claud, I'm trying to keep
the sauce, from burning.

02:11.948 --> 02:13.541
Just tell me who it is...

02:17.287 --> 02:18.629
Griffin.

02:20.081 --> 02:21.507
Hey.

02:21.666 --> 02:24.061
What are you...? I
thought you were...

02:24.085 --> 02:25.845
Yeah, I, uh,

02:26.755 --> 02:30.359
got three days leave, and I
just, you know, figured,

02:30.383 --> 02:32.435
how could I come
home and not say hi?

02:34.971 --> 02:36.481
I could answer that.

